                "id": "f9a5361eeeea65ecd402321cb5a2e742",
                "type": "phrase",
                "display_language_text": "In \"Berlin\", they **have been building** a new airport since September 2006.",
                "learn_language_text": "In \"Berlin\" **wird** seit September 2006 ein neuer ((f|*F))lughafen **gebaut**.",
                "info_text": "Der BER hat \"tatsächlich\" eröffnet, aber wegen Corona gibt es fast keine Flüge. Wer braucht schon Flughäfen!",
                "image": null,
                "sound": {
                  "id": "d3572193477785b1bc030cdf61ec777c"
                },
                "speaker_role": "f1"
              },
              {
                "id": "f9a3361eeeea65ecd402321cb5a2e742",
                "type": "task",
                "display_language_text": "The old airport (called 'Tegel') will be **transformed** into something new. There is also a plan to make it accesible by U- or S-Bahn \"now\", after it has been closed. As if that wouldn't have been a good idea while it was still an airport..",
                "learn_language_text": null,
                "info_text": null,
                "image": null,
                "sound": null,
                "speaker_role": "f1"
              },

              {
                "id": "b3496c3e514ffcfa66d7874988a50cfc",
                "type": "phrase",
                "display_language_text": "It is called **'BER'**, and there are \"many\" jokes about it.",
                "learn_language_text": "Er heißt **'BER'**, und ((*es|*right|ef)) gibt \"eine Menge\" Witze über ihn.",
                "info_text": null,
                "image": null,
                "sound": {
